    "narrative": "The Austin Waves are setting up for a high-ceiling Saturday, anchored by the elite 74.59 efficiency rating of **Kyle Tucker**. Facing an opportunistic matchup against Shota Imanaga, **Kyle Tucker** benefits from a favorable wind forecast and a solid order position, making him our primary engine for power and stolen base upside. We also see tremendous value in **Jackson Merrill** (67.91) and **Josh Lowe** (66.91), both of whom leverage significant platoon advantages against their respective right-handed opponents. While **Josh Lowe** is a top-tier play, managers should monitor the 45% rain risk in his contest, as any delays could jeopardize his contribution to our daily categories. Similarly, **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** remains a staple in our 1B slot with a strong 66.71 score, bolstered by a favorable park factor and a solid xwOBA projection against the opponent's pitching staff.\n\nOur most difficult roster decision today centered on **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.**, who missed the starting cut with a 51.98 score. While he possesses some intriguing secondary tools, he was edged out by the superior platoon and situational utility provided by **Nasim Nunez** and **Andy Pages**. We prioritized the speed-first profile of **Nasim Nunez** to maintain our competitive edge in the stolen base category, while **Andy Pages** maintains his spot due to a more favorable wind trajectory and projected order security. We are also keeping a close eye on **Gunnar Henderson**; despite his elite pedigree, his score is tempered to 53.01 today due to a tough draw against a high-skill lefty, Connelly Early. With the lineup still pending for several starters like **Drake Baldwin** and **Liam Hicks**, we will be monitoring pre-game news closely to ensure our optimization holds firm before first pitch.",
